Dialogue: Who gave them the timeline?
Oooooh! Get him.
Nothing on me? Big graphic of Darwin? This— It diminishes my
role. I’m tarred with the Mencken brush so I may as well get the
goodies, right? No point joining the party if you don’t get your
little dacha?
What?
Well I need to too. I’m a wheelman.
I’m a casket wheelman. I’m on front right. Fucking front-right
wheelman. Highly visible. Front right.
‘Closure’. You little – fucking. So you can dip your beak in the
honeypot, make some arrangements?
We’ll go late. Court rulings. Possible riots. Something changes
every five fucking minutes. The Republic is wobbling like a
fucking panna cotta. And I’m harvesting eyeballs like a fucking
eyeball hoover.
Fine. Fuck off.
But save me a space. Yeah? Good space. Second row. And let
Mencken’s people know I made the call. Tell Mencken I swung
it, yeah?
It’s gridlock. You’ll be better off walking!
Fires in Baltimore. The president, is going to make a statement.
Darwin might resign. Online is peaking. I’ll be as fast as I can.
But let them know it was me!
Uh-huh. Yeah. I can only stay for twenty.
Yeah the thing about your dad is, he’s lost quite a lot of
influence over the past few days.
It’s fine. That’s fine.
So – go on. Are you ever going to explain, what happened?
How— Why you didn’t— [tell me?]
Why didn’t you tell me?
Taking the potential dad for a test drive?
Thank you. Yeah. If it wasn’t such a total fucking disaster it
would be a dream come true.
Wow. I’m sorry, Shiv.
And not to be here. I would have. I just … I am so so tired. And
I’ve been awake so long. I – I felt like I couldn’t leave?
I was the first one in with him when, after he died. I said – did
say a goodbye.
Now? I – I can’t now? We’re right in the middle.
The hotel people know me and I hate it.
